com.intel.bluetooth
Class DebugLog

java.lang.Object
  com.intel.bluetooth.DebugLog

public abstract class DebugLog
extends java.lang.Object

BlueCove log system. If enabled "-Dbluecove.debug=true" System.out.println would be used for debug. Alternatively if log4j is available in classpath Bluecove log would be redirected to log4j and can be enable using log4j configuration. The methods of this class would be removed automaticaly because they are empty if debugCompiledOut = true. This class itself will disappear from bytecode after obfuscation by proguard in this case. Change to create mini jar.
